title: ICE when specifiyng invalid `{}` as the associated type for `impl Iterator` as a return type

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code ```Rust fn get_iter(vec: &[i32]) -> impl Iterator + '_ { vec.iter() } fn main() { let vec = Vec::new(); let mut iter = get_iter(&vec); iter.next(); } ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.62.1 (e092d0b6b 2022-07-16) binary: rustc commit-hash: e092d0b6b43f2de967af0887873151bb1c0b18d3 commit-date: 2022-07-16 host: x86_64-apple-darwin release: 1.62.1 LLVM version: 14.0.5 ``` ### Error output ``` error[E0658]: associated const equality is incomplete --> src/main.rs:1:43 | 1 | fn get_iter(vec: &[i32]) -> impl Iterator + '_ { | ^^^^^^^^^ | = note: see issue #92827 for more information error: mismatch in bind of associated type, got const --> src/main.rs:1:43 | 1 | fn get_iter(vec: &[i32]) -> impl Iterator + '_ { | ^^^^^^^^^ | note: associated type defined here does not match const thread 'rustc' panicked at 'called `Option::unwrap()` on a `None` value', compiler/rustc_trait_selection/src/traits/project.rs:565:36 ```
